Lease of prebendary service: <strong>A</strong> subleases to <strong>B</strong> the baker&rsquo;s prebend for Ayyār (II), Simān (III), and Abu (V) in the Eulma&scaron;, temple of Annunītu, for the carrying out of the duty (<em>ēpi&scaron;ānūtu</em>). <strong>A</strong> himself leased this prebend from <strong>C</strong>, for the same purpose. <strong>B</strong> vouches for the continuation of the service, the punctuality of the deliveries and the quality of the meals. <strong>B&nbsp;</strong>is to pay <strong>A</strong> 2 kor of barely in lieu of the prebendary income. 2 witnesses and the scribe: &Scaron;ama&scaron;-kāṣir/Nab&ucirc;-mukīn-apli//Isinnāya. Addendum: Each party has taken a copy of the.<br />
